tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE census_data (
   id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
   first_name VARCHAR(50),
   last_name VARCHAR(50),
   age INT,
   gender VARCHAR(10),
   occupation VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE census_data (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    city VARCHAR(100),
    state VARCHAR(50),
    population INT,
    median_income DECIMAL
);

CREATE TABLE demographics (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    city VARCHAR(100),
    state VARCHAR(50),
    age_group VARCHAR(20),
    population_count INT
);

CREATE TABLE census_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    age INT,
    city VARCHAR(50),
    occupation VARCHAR(50)
)

CREATE TABLE demographics (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    age_group VARCHAR(20),
    education_level VARCHAR(50),
    income INT,
    family_size INT
)

CREATE TABLE regions (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    region_name VARCHAR(50),
    country VARCHAR(50),
    population INT,
    median_income INT
)

CREATE TABLE policies (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    policy_name VARCHAR(50),
    description TEXT,
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE CensusData (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  age INT,
  gender VARCHAR(10),
  ethnicity VARCHAR(50),
  income DECIMAL
)

CREATE TABLE PopulationStats (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  city VARCHAR(50),
  state VARCHAR(50),
  population INT,
  median_age REAL
)

CREATE TABLE EmploymentData (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  occupation VARCHAR(50),
  unemployment_rate DECIMAL,
  employed_count INT,
  total_workers INT
)

CREATE TABLE EducationStats (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  education_level VARCHAR(50),
  graduation_rate DECIMAL,
  enrolled_students INT,
  total_students INT
)

CREATE TABLE HousingData (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  property_type VARCHAR(50),
  price DECIMAL,
  bedrooms INT,
  bathrooms INT
)
